        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer290278654" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14151096057631934865">&quot;Too close a scrutiny of my mental activities might prove anything but flattering,&quot; said John Carter. If any trait exceeds his partial prowess it must be his impulse to combat. Time and again throughout the Barsoom chronicles Carter rushes to fight--for freedom, for the love of his life, for his friends, or just for the fun of a good fight.<br/><br/>Burroughs has, perhaps, descended to the level of Saturday afternoon matinee serials, but its good, clean fun. And, this time he manages to finish his story.<br/><br/>A</span>
  <span id="freeText14151096057631934865" style="display:none">"Too close a scrutiny of my mental activities might prove anything but flattering," said John Carter. If any trait exceeds his partial prowess it must be his impulse to combat. Time and again throughout the Barsoom chronicles Carter rushes to fight--for freedom, for the love of his life, for his friends, or just for the fun of a good fight.<br /><br />Burroughs has, perhaps, descended to the level of Saturday afternoon matinee serials, but its good, clean fun. And, this time he manages to finish his story.<br /><br />A fun read.</span>
